# ── Heavy media: names/locations are tracked in manifests, bytes live outside git ──
media/**
!media/README.md
!media/*/
!media/*/.gitkeep

# ── Media file types anywhere (belt-and-suspenders against accidental commits) ──
*.mp4
*.MP4
*.mov
*.MOV
*.mkv
*.webm
*.avi
*.mts
*.MTS
*.wav
*.aiff
*.flac
*.m4a
*.mp3

# Exception: nothing yet. If a tiny canonical media asset must be versioned,
# whitelist it here explicitly and consider Git LFS.

# ── Kdenlive / MLT cache & backups ──
*.kdenlive~
*.mlt.cache
*.backup
*.autosave

# ── Node / Remotion ──
node_modules/
packages/remotion-graphics/out/
packages/remotion-graphics/public/_feat/
.cache/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Reference screenshots dropped at repo root (third-party material, not assets) ──
/IMG_*.PNG
/IMG_*.png

# ── OS / editor ──
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea/

# Zipped render bundles next to out/
packages/remotion-graphics/out*.zip

# ── Per-episode assets published into Remotion's public/ by screen-chop.sh ──
# Chopped screen recordings, fan-out assets, freeze stills. All are GENERATED from media/ and are
# reproducible from tracked sources (rule 1: never commit generated media). They are neither tracked
# nor previously ignored, which means one `git add -A` would have swept ~5MB of clips per episode
# into the repo. e002's stills are hand-made source and stay tracked.
packages/remotion-graphics/public/e0*/
!packages/remotion-graphics/public/e002/
